<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-316-902  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 316 902.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 29 1989 v6 n21 p64(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Maps make numbers talk. (on-line PC mapping)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   DDB Needham Worldwide Inc. (marketing)Market Action Research Inc. (products).andO;Product:   MapWise (Computer program) (usage).andO;Topic:     MapsMarketingSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Although it's often said that numbers speak for themselves, they seldom do.andM;At DDB Needham Worldwide, an advertising agency in New York, marketingnumbers find a voice with on-line PC mapping, according to Stuart Goldberg,the agency's director of marketing decision systems.andM;On-line PC mapping uses creative graphics techniques to plot multiple dataitems -- for example, market share, geographic penetration and overall sales-- simultaneously onto a single map.andM;''We make the data talk to our clients,'' said Goldberg.andM;''Essentially, we're oriented toward modeling and quantitative analysis ofmarketing data for improving sales,'' he continued.andM;The theory is that clients can understand a picture much easier than a stackof printed tables.andM;One PC tool he uses is MapWise, from Market Action Research Inc. The package,which plots data onto a U.S.andP;  map, helps in creating business proposals,Goldberg  said.andM;Goldberg also uses it to compare changes over time in the images ofcompetitive companies.andM;Market Action, of Peoria, Ill., can be reached at (309) 677-3299.andO;</TEXT></DOC>